      • truncateDataForPut

        public boolean truncateDataForPut(byte colDefEndCode)
        Truncates the data from given timestamp to match the column definition as returned by server describe information To be used only in case on INSERT operation, note that for normal inserts server will anyway do this, however if IFX_USEPUT is set then it is driver responsibility to truncate the data for datetime column. This method ends up using deprecated methods from java.sql.Date.setXXX(), which is not a concern since all we do is set the field in the timestamp to 0
        Parameters:
        colDefEndCode -
        Returns:
        true if data was truncated
        Since:
        4.10.JC5
